### `position: sticky` with `overflow: hidden` parent

When using `position: sticky` on an element, it will not work if any of its parent elements have `overflow: hidden`, `overflow: scroll`, or `overflow: auto` applied. This is because the sticky positioning is constrained by the scroll container.

**Example:**
```css
/* This will NOT work */
.parent {
  overflow: hidden;
}

.child {
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
}
```

**Solution:** Remove the `overflow` property from the parent, or use a different layout approach.

---

### CSS Custom Properties (Variables) with `calc()`

CSS custom properties can be used in `calc()` expressions, but they must be properly formatted. When using a custom property in `calc()`, ensure the variable is defined and accessible in the same scope.

**Example:**
```css
:root {
  --spacing: 16px;
}

.element {
  padding: calc(var(--spacing) * 2); /* Works */
  margin: calc(var(--spacing) / 2); /* Works */
}
```

**Note:** If the custom property is not defined, `calc()` will use the inherited value or default to `0`.

---

### `:focus-visible` for keyboard navigation

The `:focus-visible` pseudo-class applies styles only when the element is focused and the user is navigating via keyboard (not mouse clicks). This is useful for accessibility, as it avoids showing focus rings on mouse clicks.

**Example:**
```css
button:focus-visible {
  outline: 2px solid blue;
  outline-offset: 2px;
}
```

**Browser Support:** Works in all modern browsers (Chrome 86+, Firefox 85+, Safari 15.4+).

